{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775845577535,"sessionID":"ses_2875b0f1cffexK7aoZm6r9C9Vy","part":{"id":"prt_d78a5131e001H4GVlAKuZE4c6J","messageID":"msg_d78a501d4001287fjwy6erSLZ6","sessionID":"ses_2875b0f1cffexK7aoZm6r9C9Vy","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-34d0cabfd947422faffc09f88fbec9cf","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-006/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-006/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理 Implementation Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n4: **Language**: Go\n5: **Size**: M\n6: **Design Stage**: ST-3 Completed\n7: \n8: ## Task Breakdown\n9: \n10: ### Task 1: Create package structure and initialize constants\n11: - [ ] Verify `pkg/workloadmanager` directory exists\n12: - [ ] Create `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` (if not exists) - Define timeout and configuration constants\n13:   - [ ] Define `DefaultSandboxTTL = 8 * time.Hour`\n14:   - [ ] Define `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout = 15 * time.Minute`\n15:   - [ ] Define `GCInterval = 15 * time.Second`\n16:   - [ ] Define `GCSingleTickTimeout = 2 * time.Minute`\n17:   - [ ] Define `DeleteTimeout = 30 * time.Second`\n18:   - [ ] Define label constants:\n19:     - [ ] `SessionIDLabelKey = \"runtime.agentcube.io/session-id\"`\n20:     - [ ] `WorkloadNameLabelKey = \"runtime.agentcube.io/workload-name\"`\n21:     - [ ] `SandboxNameLabelKey = \"runtime.agentcube.io/sandbox-name\"`\n22:     - [ ] `ManagedByLabel = \"managed-by\"`\n23:     - [ ] `ManagedByValue = \"agentcube-workload-manager\"`\n24:   - [ ] Define annotation constants:\n25:     - [ ] `LastActivityAnnotationKey = \"last-activity-time\"`\n26:     - [ ] `IdleTimeoutAnnotationKey = \"runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout\"`\n27: - [ ] Create `pkg/workloadmanager/types/sandbox_types.go` (if not exists) - Define sandbox lifecycle types\n28:   - [ ] Define `SandboxCleanupReason` type\n29:   - [ ] Define constants: `CleanupReasonManual`, `CleanupReasonIdleTimeout`, `CleanupReasonExpired`\n30:   - [ ] Define `CleanupAuditEntry` struct\n31:     - [ ] SessionID, SandboxID, Namespace, Reason, DeletedAt, Success, ErrorMessage\n32: - [ ] Define GVR constants for Sandbox resources\n33:   - [ ] `SandboxGVR` for agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1/Sandbox\n34:   - [ ] `SandboxClaimGVR` for extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1/SandboxClaim\n35: - [ ] Verify package compiles: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n36: \n37: **Verification**: Run `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` to ensure the package structure and constants compile\n38: \n39: ---\n40: \n41: ### Task 2: Implement Store interface extensions for lifecycle management\n42: - [ ] Extend `pkg/store/store.go` Store interface (if not already extended)\n43:   - [ ] Implement `StoreSandbox(ctx, sessionID string, info *types.SandboxInfo) error`\n44:   - [ ] Implement `GetSandbox(ctx, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n45:   - [ ] Implement `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sessionID string, info *types.SandboxInfo) error`\n46:   - [ ] Implement `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID string) error`\n47:   - [ ] Implement `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, since time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n48:   - [ ] Implement `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, threshold time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n49: - [ ] Create unit tests for Store interface methods in `pkg/store/store_test.go`\n50:   - [ ] Test StoreSandbox and GetSandbox\n51:   - [ ] Test UpdateSandbox\n52:   - [ ] Test DeleteSandboxBySessionID\n53:   - [ ] Test ListInactiveSandboxes with valid time threshold\n54:   - [ ] Test ListExpiredSandboxes with valid threshold\n55:   - [ ] Test error handling for non-existent sessions\n56: \n57: **Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/store -run TestStore` to verify Store interface tests pass\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: ### Task 3: Implement Kubernetes client wrapper for deletion operations\n62: - [ ] Extend `pkg/workloadmanager/client/k8s_client.go` Client interface (if not already extended)\n63:   - [ ] Implement `DeleteSandbox(ctx, namespace, name string) error`\n64:   - [ ] Ensure GetAgentRuntime method exists\n65:   - [ ] Ensure GetCodeInterpreter method exists\n66:   - [ ] Ensure CreateSandbox method exists\n67: - [ ] Implement DeleteSandbox method\n68:   - [ ] Determine GVR based on resource type (Sandbox or SandboxClaim)\n69:   - [ ] Use dynamic client to delete resource\n70:   - [ ] Handle NotFound errors gracefully (return nil, not error)\n71:   - [ ] Return error for other deletion failures\n72: - [ ] Create or extend unit tests in `pkg/workloadmanager/client/k8s_client_test.go`\n73:   - [ ] Test DeleteSandbox for Sandbox resource\n74:   - [ ] Test DeleteSandbox for SandboxClaim resource\n75:   - [ ] Test DeleteSandbox with NotFound error (should succeed)\n76:   - [ ] Test DeleteSandbox with other errors (should fail)\n77:   - [ ] Test GetAgentRuntime and GetCodeInterpreter (if not tested)\n78: \n79: **Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/client -run TestK8sClient` to verify K8sClient tests pass\n80: \n81: ---\n82: \n83: ### Task 4: Implement SandboxController deletion methods\n84: - [ ] Create or extend `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/sandbox.go`\n85: - [ ] Define SandboxController struct (if not exists)\n86:   - [ ] `k8sClient client.Client` - Kubernetes client\n87:   - [ ] `store store.Store` - Session store\n88: - [ ] Implement `DeleteSession(ctx, sessionID string) (*api.DeleteSessionResponse, error)`\n89:   - [ ] Retrieve sandbox metadata from store via store.GetSandbox\n90:   - [ ] Return error if not found\n91:   - [ ] Delete sandbox resource from Kubernetes via k8sClient.DeleteSandbox\n92:   - [ ] Handle NotFound error gracefully (continue to store deletion)\n93:   - [ ] Delete session record from store via store.Dele